snippet.title: Blacklite District (Kyle Pfeiffer) Origins, Minecraft & Danger Taint | Full Interview | The SDR Show
snippet.description:
Blacklite District, Kyle Pfeiffer, joins Ralph Sutton and James Mattern and they discuss the name of the band, how Kyle started out writing songs to cope with his mother's passing, then handling the death of his father shortly after. Blacklite District talks about getting a drum kit from his grandparents as a kid, their connection to the gamer community (especially Roblox and Minecraft), and what's to come in 2022. Blacklite District (Kyle Pfeiffer) also talks his first concert, first drug and first sexual experience!

(Air Date: November 24th, 2021)

The SDR Show merchandise is available at https://podcastmerch.com/collections/the-sdr-show 

You can watch The SDR Show LIVE for FREE every Wednesday and Saturday at 9pm ET at https://www.GaSDigitalNetwork.com/LIVE. New episodes will be available on YouTube every Sunday and Thursday at 9PM ET.
 
Once you're there you can sign up at GaSDigitalNetwork.com with promo code: SDR for a 14-day FREE trial with access to every SDR show ever recorded and ALL the shows that GaS Digital Network has to offer! 

The SDR Show (The Sex, Drugs, & Rock-n-Roll Show) is hosted by comedian Big Jay Oakerson and legendary radio host Ralph Sutton. SDR is a no-apologies, not politically correct, not for the faint of heart show that somehow blends the classic energy of a morning radio show into the new era of digital entertainment.
